{"type":"click","text":"A\n          \n            Single Scene + Swappable Content\n            One main scene holds the sidebar permanently. Screen content is loaded/unloaded into a container node. Simple, flat structure.\n            Recommended\n          \n        \n        MainScene.tscn\n├── Sidebar (always visible, handles nav clicks)\n├── ContentContainer (swaps child scenes)\n│   └── [current screen] (HabitatFloor / Shop / Orders / ...)\n├── TransitionOverlay (crossfade + fade-to-black layers)\n└── ImmersiveLayer (story events, level-up — above everything)\n        \n          \n            Pros\n            \n              Sidebar never rebuilds — state preserved\n              Clear ownership: MainScene manages all transitions\n              Easy to reason about — one scene tree\n              Screens are independent .tscn files\n            \n          \n          \n            Cons\n            \n              All screens share one tree — careful with signals\n              Memory: previous screen fully unloaded","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776055333372}
